@startuml
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/main/proveo.puml
title Aphelion — Overview · Authority & Governance\n//layer 03 — transport / Telegram surface omitted//
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultFontSize 12

package "Authority & Governance" as AUTH {
  component "**effectauth**\ncommand-effect authorization\nallow / deny membrane\n//approval narrows, never widens//" as EAUTH <<error>>
  component "**principal**\nidentity & authorization model\nadmin / user · scope · session ownership" as PRIN <<app>>
  component "**interpretation**\njudgment / use ledger service\n//says what happened, grants nothing//" as INTERP <<app>>
  component "**decision**\ntyped operator-decision records" as DEC <<app>>
}

' --- neighbouring layers ---
rectangle "Composition & Orchestration\n//-> 01-orchestration//" as ORCH <<app>>
rectangle "Capabilities & I/O\n//-> 04-capabilities//" as CAP <<app>>
database  "State & Continuity\n//-> 06-state//" as STATE <<db>>

ORCH ARROW_OPTIONAL EAUTH : authorize effect
CAP  ARROW_OPTIONAL EAUTH : gate capability
ORCH ARROW_OPTIONAL PRIN  : resolve principal

EAUTH  ARROW_OPTIONAL STATE : read leases / grants
INTERP ARROW_OPTIONAL STATE : record judgments
DEC    ARROW_OPTIONAL STATE : decision records

note bottom of AUTH
  Classification says **what** an effect is;
  **effectauth** says whether this principal may
  perform it **now**. Authority is granted by an
  approved lease/grant — never by interpretation.
end note

@enduml
